text: The 2002 United States Soccer Federation presidential election was held in San Francisco on August 9, 2002 to determine the next President of the United States Soccer Federation. Robert Contiguglia ran unopposed. Contiguglia has been involved in soccer in the U.S. for more than three decades, during which he has excelled at almost every level of the game. ==References== Category:Presidents of the United States Soccer Federation Category:2002 in American soccer
title: 2002 United States Soccer Federation presidential election
